President Biden, Secretary of State Blinken, and Secretary of Defense Austin met with Ukraine's Foreign Minister Kuleba and Minister of Defense Reznikov to discuss Ukraine's military, diplomatic, and humanitarian situation. The President updated the ministers on US efforts to support Ukraine in its fight against Russian aggression, including through meetings in Belgium and the provision of military and humanitarian assistance. They also discussed ongoing actions to hold President Putin accountable for Russia's aggression, including new sanctions announced by President Biden in Brussels.